<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25650</anchor> <rss>anon.169.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.169</addr>  <route>anon.169.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>s \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a section of <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>; if <tex>b_0</tex> is the centre of contraction of <tex>B</tex>, then the centre of contraction of <tex>A</tex> is given by <tex>rb_0</tex>. For the rest, we use the fact that <link href="erct-0026.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0026" title="Propositions are closed under retracts">propositions are closed under retracts</link> and <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">contractible types are propositions</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25651</anchor> <rss>erct-0027.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-0027</addr>  <route>erct-0027.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">Contractible</link> types are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0027.agda" type="external">erct-0027.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>B</tex> and <tex>B</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>, then <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25652</anchor> <rss>erct-0026.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0026</addr>  <route>erct-0026.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">Propositions</link> are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0026.agda" type="external">erct-0026.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>B</tex> and <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, then <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25653</anchor> <rss>anon.170.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.170</addr>  <route>anon.170.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>This can be seen using the cancellation laws of retractions.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25654</anchor> <rss>erct-001K.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001K</addr>  <route>erct-001K.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">Contractible</link> types are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">propositions</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001K.agda" type="external">erct-001K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25655</anchor> <rss>anon.180.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.180</addr>  <route>anon.180.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>As <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link> with some centre <tex>a:A</tex>, we have for any <tex>x,y:A</tex> identifications <tex>\chi _x  \colon  a = x</tex> and <tex>\chi _y \colon  a = y</tex>. Therefore, we identify <tex>x</tex> with <tex>y</tex> using <tex>\chi _x ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _y</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>